item.title: CVE-2017-14806|2024-09-16T16:48:59.649Z -- suse -- studio%20onsite
item.description: A Improper Certificate Validation vulnerability in susestudio-common of SUSE Studio onsite allows remote attackers to MITM connections to the repositories, which allows the modification of packages received over these connections. This issue affects: SUSE Studio onsite susestudio-common version 1.3.17-56.6.3 and prior versions.
